        {
          "type": "assistant",
          "text": "Cool idea — an entertainment plugin that teaches LeetCode while agents work in the background. I can see this being a Claude Code plugin/skill.\n\nFirst clarifying question:\n\n**Where should this plugin live?** \n\n- **(A)** As a new skill inside the existing superpowers plugin (alongside brainstorming, TDD, etc.)\n- **(B)** As a standalone Claude Code plugin in its own repo (e.g., `leetcode-tutor` or similar)\n- **(C)** As a skill within this `dosty` repo specifically\n\nI'd recommend **(B)** — a standalone plugin — since it's not related to superpowers' development workflow and could be useful across any project. What do you think?",
