        {
          "type": "assistant",
          "text": "Good call. Next question:\n\n**How should the LeetCode problems be sourced?**\n\n- **(A)** Bundled — ship a curated set of problems (e.g., 50-100 classic ones) as JSON/markdown files inside the plugin itself. Works offline, no API dependency.\n- **(B)** Fetched live — pull problems from LeetCode's API or a third-party API at runtime. Always fresh, but adds network dependency.\n- **(C)** Hybrid — bundle a core set, but optionally fetch more if network is available.\n\nI'd recommend **(A)** — bundled. It's simpler, always works, avoids rate-limiting issues, and the classic problems (Two Sum, Valid Parentheses, etc.) don't change. What do you think?",
