          "text": "\n\nNext question:\n\n**What difficulty level should the problems target, and should users be able to configure this?**\n\n- **(A)** Easy only — keep it light and fun, quick to digest while waiting\n- **(B)** Mixed (Easy/Medium) with random selection — some variety but nothing too heavy\n- **(C)** User-configurable — let users set preferred difficulty in plugin settings (easy/medium/hard)\n- **(D)** Progressive — start easy, get harder over time as the user sees more problems\n\nI'd lean toward **(C)** — configurable with a default of Easy/Medium mix. People have different skill levels and some might enjoy Hard problems during long agent runs. What's your preference?",
