        {
          "type": "assistant",
          "text": "\n\nNext question:\n\n**How should the step-by-step explanations be structured?**\n\n- **(A)** Pre-written — each bundled problem includes a full written walkthrough (approach, pseudocode, solution, complexity analysis). Deterministic, fast, no LLM cost.\n- **(B)** LLM-generated — the subagent generates explanations on-the-fly using Claude. More conversational, can adapt to user level, but uses tokens.\n- **(C)** Hybrid — bundle the problem statement and hints, but let the subagent explain interactively (user can ask follow-up questions like \"why not use a hash map here?\")\n\nI'd recommend **(A)** — pre-written. Since the whole point is entertainment *while waiting*, we don't want the tutor itself consuming significant tokens or competing with the working agent. Fast and predictable. What do you think?",
