        {
          "type": "assistant",
          "text": "\n\nNext question:\n\n**How should the plugin activate?**\n\n- **(A)** Automatically — whenever a background agent is dispatched, the LeetCode tutor subagent launches alongside it without the user asking\n- **(B)** Manual — user triggers it explicitly (e.g., `/leetcode` command) when they want entertainment\n- **(C)** Opt-in auto — user enables it in settings, then it auto-launches whenever background agents run\n\nI'd recommend **(C)** — opt-in auto. Automatic without consent would be annoying, but requiring manual trigger every time defeats the \"entertainment while waiting\" purpose. A setting like `\"leetcode_tutor\": true` feels right. What do you think?",
