          "type": "assistant",
          "text": "\n\nNext question:\n\n**How should the problem be presented — all at once or interactively?**\n\n- **(A)** Full dump — show the problem, then the complete step-by-step walkthrough in one message. User reads at their own pace.\n- **(B)** Paced reveal — show the problem first, then reveal hints/steps one at a time with pauses, so the user can try to think before seeing the next step.\n- **(C)** Try-first — show the problem, ask \"want to try it yourself or see the solution?\", then reveal based on response.\n\nI'd recommend **(B)** — paced reveal. It's more engaging and educational. Show the problem, pause, then reveal approach, then pseudocode, then solution, then complexity. Keeps the user thinking rather than just passively reading. What do you think?",
